            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>Condition of the Country</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>There can be no excuse for restless efforts to disturb the tranquility into
                    which the public mind is disposed to subside.</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>SS takes exception to American tendency to complain about the United
                    States. It is actually in fine shape; prosperous, lots of land, relative social
                    peace, free from disease outbreaks, bountiful resources. People should look to
                    the positive.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>Telegraph Line Complete</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>Staunton is now in communication with the rest of the big cities and needs
                    only a little "gas" (which some of our neighbors are uncharitable enough to
                    insinuate we are already overstocked with) to make her a "finished" place.</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Telegraph line betweeen Richmond and Staunton has been completed. Text of
                    first messages to and from the SS and Richmond Whig. Complains about
                    interference from Waynesboro and Charlottesville</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>Kansas and the Vindicator</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Comments on Vindicator's coverage of Kansas. Refers to a Vinidcator article
                    entitled "Kansas and the Spectator."</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>3</column>
                <head>Railroad Excursion</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Four or five hundred Stauntonians took an excursion to the Central Railraod
                    terminus in Oakland, Allegheny Co. Describes the speeches and festivities.
                    Staunton Glee Club participated.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>3</column>
                <head>Presbyterian (New School) Convention</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Report on meeting of Southern Presbyterians in Richmond. The Synod split
                    over slavery. Debate over the wisdom of organizing a sectional church.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>3</column>
                <head>Photographs</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Rankin</ln>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Urges readers to go to Rankin's gallery to see new photographs of a citizen
                    of Staunton.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>3</column>
                <head>Coming In</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Chapman</ln>
                        <pf>Wm.</pf>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>SS is looking forward to a promising harvest of "vegetable curiosities",
                    like Chapmans multi-eared ear of corn.</summary>
            </div>
